# All experiment outputs stay local. Scripts and the interpretive
# summary.md are tracked; everything that lands under
# experiments/bias_pruning/results/ (per-utterance CSVs, per-seed
# summaries, comparison tables, plots, descriptive tables) is not.
# Both evaluate_subgroup_wer.py and compare_conditions.py create
# subdirs as needed, so the folder doesn't need to exist in git.
# This also forecloses any chance of a Fair-Speech / CORAAL /
# L2-ARCTIC transcript ending up in a committed CSV.
experiments/bias_pruning/results/